\begin_layout Standard
The total work is obtained by integrating 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta W$
\end_inset

 over the path of the applied force:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
W=\underbrace{\varoint}_{path}\vec{F}\cdot d\vec{x}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example, when we lift a from the floor to the table as illustrated in
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:barbell lifting"

\end_inset

 we increase the gravitational potential energy, 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

, of the barbell by an amount 
\begin_inset Formula $mgh$
\end_inset

, where:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 = the mass of the barbell
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 = the gravitational acceleration (9.8 m/s
\begin_inset Formula $^{2}$
\end_inset

)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $h_{f}$
\end_inset

 = the final resting height of the barbell above the floor
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Because the potential energy only depends only on the final resting location
 of the barbell, it is a state variable.
 The work we expend in putting the barbell there depends on the path we
 took to get it there, however.
 As a result this work is NOT a state function.
 Suppose, for example that we lift the barbell to a maximum height 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{max}$
\end_inset

 and then drop it onto the table.
 The work, 
\begin_inset Formula $W$
\end_inset

, we expended is equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $mgh_{max}$
\end_inset

, which is greater than the increase in potential energy, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta U$
\end_inset

.
 The difference between between 
\begin_inset Formula $W$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta U$
\end_inset

 is the irreversable work and corresponds to energy dissipated as heat,
 permanent deformation of the table, etc.
 We'll return to the distinction between reversible and irreversible work
 later.
 
\end_layout

